itiated the non-sectarian study of this thirteenth-century figure and in effect commenced what are called Dо̄gen Studies [Dagen kenkyii] in modern times.As one way of exploring what it might possibly mean to say that Dо̄gen "belongs to mankind," the Kuroda Institute held a conference on Dо̄gen at Tassajara Springs, California from October 8 to 10, 1981. The essays of this volume are a part of its result.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / Zen (see also PHILOSOPHY / Zen).2bisacsh1 aAbe, Masao, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBellah, Robert N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBielefeldt, Carl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCook, Francis H ., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKasulis, Thomas P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKim, Hee-Jin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaFleur, William R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaFleur, William R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMaraldo, John C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311056415040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082484135540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824841355423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780824841355/original  a978-3-11-056415-0  University of Hawaii Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13EN